I"Í<p>This tracker discovers new devices on boot and tracks Bluetooth devices periodically based on <code>interval_seconds</code> value. It is not required to pair the devices with each other! Devices discovered are stored with ‚Äòbt_‚Äô as the prefix for device MAC addresses in <code>known_devices.yaml</code>.</p>
<p>This platform requires pybluez to be installed. On Debian based installs, run</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash">sudo apt install bluetooth libbluetooth-dev
</code></pre>
<p>To use the Bluetooth tracker in your installation, add the following to your <code>configuration.yaml</code> file:</p>
<pre><code class="language-yaml"># Example configuration.yaml entry
device_tracker:
  - platform: bluetooth_tracker
</code></pre>
<div class="config-vars">
  <h3><a class="title-link" name="configuration-variables" href="#configuration-variables"></a> Configuration Variables</h3>
  <dl class=''><dt><a class='title-link' name='request_rssi' href='#request_rssi'></a> request_rssi</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='boolean'>boolean</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Optional)</span><span class='description'><p>Performs a request for the ‚ÄúReceived signal strength indication‚Äù (RSSI) of each tracked device.</p>
</span></p><p class='default'>
Default value: <p>false</p>
</p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='device_id' href='#device_id'></a> device_id</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='integer'>integer</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Optional)</span><span class='description'><p>The ID of the bluetooth adapter to be used by the tracker, e.g., use <code>0</code> for <code>hci0</code>, <code>1</code> for <code>hci1</code>, and so on.</p>
</span></p><p class='default'>
Default value: <p><code>-1</code> (The first available bluetooth adapter)</p>
</p></dd></dl>
</div>
<p>In some cases it can be that your device is not discovered. In that case let your phone scan for Bluetooth devices while you restart Home Assistant. Just hit <code>Scan</code> on your phone all the time until Home Assistant is fully restarted and the device should appear in <code>known_devices.yaml</code>.</p>
<p>For additional configuration variables check the <a href="/integrations/device_tracker/">Device tracker page</a>.</p>
